'''Ivan Ivanavich Antanovich''' ({{lang-be|Іван Іванавіч Антановіч}}, {{lang-ru|Иван Иванович Антонович}} born 3 April 1937) is a Belarusian sociologist, linguist, political scientist, philosopher, diplomat, and politician. He was a professor of sociology in 1973 and a doctorate for [[Doktor nauk]] in 1977. He is a founder of the [[Republican Party of Labour and Justice]]. He was the [[Ministry of Foreign Affairs (Belarus)|Minister of Foreign Affairs for Belarus]] from 1997 to 1998. He speaks fluent Belarusian, Russian and English.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mfa.gov.by/en/ministry/staff/|publisher=mfa.gov.by|title=Minister and Deputy Ministers - Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Belarus|access-date=19 February 2017}}</ref><ref> [http://www.biografija.ru/show_bio.aspx?id=4749 Біографія Івана Антоновича] (Russian)</ref>

== Personal life ==
He was born in the village of [[Damašy]] in the [[Second Polish Republic]] (now [[Poland]]) in 1937 to a Polish father and mother. He graduated at Kazan Federal University in Russia. In 1969, he was working at the Secretariat in the [[United Nations]] in the [[UNESCO]]. In 1977, he was a head secretary of [[Minsk City CPB]] and later was the head of Culture and Department of [[Communist Party of Byelorussia]]. rom 1990 to 1991 - Deputy Head of the Department of the Central Committee of links with social and political organizations. From 1990 to 1991 he was the member of the Political Bureau of the Communist Party of the RSFSR. From 1990 to 1991, he was the Secretary of the Communist Party of the RSFSR Relations socio-political organizations. From 1991 to 1993 he worked in the international non-governmental research and educational organization "Rau-Corporation." He served as the Deputy Minister of Foreign Affairs of the Republic of Belarus from 1996 to 1997. He is married and has two children.
